[0m[49m[39m  302, 322[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  303, 323[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  304, 324[0m:[39m[49m **Step 3: Batch scoring.** Every night, the scoring pipeline runs all open balances through the trained model and calibration layer. Each balance gets a propensity score (0.0 to 1.0) and the top contributing features (for explainability to collection staff). The results are written to DynamoDB for fast lookup. Skip this step and your collection team is flying blind, treating every balance the same regardless of likelihood of recovery.
